    <bodyText>
      <Value><![CDATA[<p id="speakable-summary" style="background-repeat: no-repeat; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 15px 0px; color: #333333; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: -0.1px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Businesses often encounter challenges in configuring their customer relationship management (CRM) platforms, whether because of requirements specific to their organization or industry or a lack of institutional technical knowledge. In the worst case, the consequences can be severe. A 2021 <a style="background-repeat: no-repeat; box-sizing: inherit; background-color: transparent; touch-action: manipulation; text-decoration: none; color: #00a562; border-bottom: 1px solid #f1f1f1; transition: color 0s ease 0s, border-color 0.2s linear 0s;" rel="noopener" href="https://www.forbes.com/sites/quickerbettertech/2021/02/19/on-crm-48-percent-say-that-their-crm-system-doesnt-meet-their-needs-the-good-news-is-that-this-is-fixable/?sh=72b54b5d6969" target="_blank">survey</a> from CRM software vendor SugarCRM found that 50% of companies don’t know how to access customer data across their marketing, sales and service systems, while 53% said the administrative burdens of their CRM software causes friction for their sales team.</p>
<p style="background-repeat: no-repeat; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 15px 0px; color: #333333; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: -0.1px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Aiming to lighten the development load around Salesforce’s ecosystem in particular, <a style="background-repeat: no-repeat; box-sizing: inherit; background-color: transparent; touch-action: manipulation; text-decoration: none; color: #00a562; border-bottom: 1px solid #f1f1f1; transition: color 0s ease 0s, border-color 0.2s linear 0s;" rel="noopener" href="http://sweep.io/" target="_blank">Sweep</a> today emerged from stealth with a no-code toolkit for building sales playbooks in Salesforce’s CRM software. The startup is well-capitalized, with $28 million in equity financing from Bessemer Venture Partners (which seeded Sweep) and Insight Partners (which led the company’s most recent round, a Series A).</p>
<p style="background-repeat: no-repeat; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 15px 0px; color: #333333; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: -0.1px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Said Bessemer’s Adam Fisher in an emailed statement: “Modern businesses constantly make changes to their business operations to drive productivity and efficiency, but are held back due to a reliance on system integrators. Sweep’s no-code approach empowers Salesforce users to take back the reins, and makes Salesforce a more agile and responsive platform.”</p>
<div class="container__access-control" style="background-repeat: no-repeat; box-sizing: inherit; color: #333333; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: -0.1px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;"></div>
<p style="background-repeat: no-repeat; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 15px 0px; color: #333333; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: -0.1px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Sweep was co-founded by Ido Gaver, who says he experienced the pain of managing business processes on CRM platforms firsthand over the last 10 years — both as an admin and a manager of go-to-market teams. Gaver previously co-launched Flok, a customer loyalty platform, which was acquired by Wix in 2019. Gaver stayed on at Wix for three years as general manager of Wix’s business-to-business division before starting Sweep in July 2021.</p>
<p style="background-repeat: no-repeat; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 15px 0px; color: #333333; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: -0.1px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Eran Kirshenboim, Sweep’s other co-founder, also helped co-launch Flok. Kirshenboim worked alongside Gaver at Wix until they left the company together in early 2021.</p>
<p style="background-repeat: no-repeat; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 15px 0px; color: #333333; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: -0.1px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;"> </p>
<p style="background-repeat: no-repeat; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 15px 0px; color: #333333; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: -0.1px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">“The lack of agility and the gap between how go-to-market processes are managed versus online funnels were constant areas of frustration [for Sweep’s co-founders], including me,” Gaver told TechCrunch in an email interview. “Moreover, we saw how difficult it was for the revenue operations team to do their job — how they constantly struggled between different areas of responsibility — and we decided that we want to create a tool that would change their day-to-day.”</p>
<p style="background-repeat: no-repeat; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 15px 0px; color: #333333; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: -0.1px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">To add to Gaver’s point, CRM deployment can prove to be a costly endeavor when dealing with a company lacking in in-house CRM development skills. CRM firm Close <a style="background-repeat: no-repeat; box-sizing: inherit; background-color: transparent; touch-action: manipulation; text-decoration: none; color: #00a562; border-bottom: 1px solid #f1f1f1; transition: color 0s ease 0s, border-color 0.2s linear 0s;" rel="noopener" href="https://www.close.com/guides-content/crm-implementation-cost#:~:text=On%20average%2C%20a%20CRM%20implementation,productivity%20during%20the%20migration%20process." target="_blank">pegs</a> the bill at between $10,000 to $20,000 for a sales team of around 10 users, which includes the time spent choosing and implementing a CRM and expenses for consulting, training and reduced productivity during the migration process.</p>
<div class="midarticle-ad-wrapper" style="background-repeat: no-repeat; box-sizing: inherit; clear: both; width: 740.8px; color: #333333; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: -0.1px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">
<div class="container__access-control" style="background-repeat: no-repeat; box-sizing: inherit;"></div>
</div>
<p style="background-repeat: no-repeat; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 15px 0px; color: #333333; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: -0.1px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Sweep sits adjacent to installed Salesforce software, allowing teams to create and update sales funnels — the marketing term for the journey potential customers go through on their way to purchase a product. Abstracting away the typical Salesforce code and validation rules, Sweep provides templates for adding funnels to Salesforce and provides guidance for managing data within existing Salesforce layouts.</p>
<p style="background-repeat: no-repeat; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 15px 0px; color: #333333; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: -0.1px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">With Sweep, users can create and visualize CRM processes, rules and automations with drag-and-drop tools while the platform constructs the necessary backend infrastructure in Salesforce. For posterity, Sweep records a log for processes and generates reports for all the elements in a funnel.</p>
<p style="background-repeat: no-repeat; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 15px 0px; color: #333333; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: -0.1px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">“We believe that traditional solutions result in over-complication which loses deals and limits a company’s ability to achieve its growth potential. [Moreover, there’s a] shortage of skilled Salesforce admins to support the growth of the ecosystem; companies are struggling to hire talented admins to support their growth,” Gaver said. “These days, when companies are trying to save money and cut costs, Sweep’s no-code editor helps them to run a lean operation without relying on external resources.”</p>
<p style="background-repeat: no-repeat; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 15px 0px; color: #333333; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: -0.1px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Sweep is one of a number of vendors building businesses around Salesforce’s growing CRM portfolio. On the DevOps side, there’s <a style="background-repeat: no-repeat; box-sizing: inherit; background-color: transparent; touch-action: manipulation; text-decoration: none; color: #00a562; border-bottom: 1px solid #f1f1f1; transition: color 0s ease 0s, border-color 0.2s linear 0s;" href="https://techcrunch.com/2022/06/22/software-devops-platform-gearset-raises-55m/">Gearset</a>, a tooling provider for Salesforce software, as well as <a style="background-repeat: no-repeat; box-sizing: inherit; background-color: transparent; touch-action: manipulation; text-decoration: none; color: #00a562; border-bottom: 1px solid #f1f1f1; transition: color 0s ease 0s, border-color 0.2s linear 0s;" rel="noopener" href="https://techcrunch.com/2022/05/04/autorabit-which-develops-tooling-for-salesforce-crm-devs-lands-26m/" target="_blank">AutoRabit</a> and Copado. It’s certainly a lucrative market to chase after, given that global spending on CRM software is projected to reach $49.6 billion by 2025 (<a style="background-repeat: no-repeat; box-sizing: inherit; background-color: transparent; touch-action: manipulation; text-decoration: none; color: #00a562; border-bottom: 1px solid #f1f1f1; transition: color 0s ease 0s, border-color 0.2s linear 0s;" rel="noopener" href="https://www.statista.com/statistics/605933/worldwide-customer-relationship-management-market-forecast/" target="_blank">according</a> to Statista) and that Salesforce had a 32.2% share of the CRM segment in 2021 (by one <a style="background-repeat: no-repeat; box-sizing: inherit; background-color: transparent; touch-action: manipulation; text-decoration: none; color: #00a562; border-bottom: 1px solid #f1f1f1; transition: color 0s ease 0s, border-color 0.2s linear 0s;" rel="noopener" href="https://www.appsruntheworld.com/top-10-crm-software-vendors-and-market-forecast/" target="_blank">estimate</a>).</p>
<div class="midarticle-ad-wrapper" style="background-repeat: no-repeat; box-sizing: inherit; clear: both; width: 740.8px; color: #333333; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: -0.1px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">
<div class="container__access-control" style="background-repeat: no-repeat; box-sizing: inherit;"></div>
</div>
<p style="background-repeat: no-repeat; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 15px 0px; color: #333333; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: -0.1px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">The sizeable investments in Sweep to date are a strong bet on its future success. It’s been a slow ramp-up for the 30-person startup, though — Gaver only named two customers, Empathy.com and Demostack, and declined to reveal the revenue is coming in.</p>]]></Value>
